HB 844 Original 2026 Regular Session Fontenot
Abstract: Defines the term "school zone" for purposes of the prohibition against the use of
wireless telecommunications devices while operating a motor vehicle.
Present law (R.S. 32:59) prohibits the operation of a wireless telecommunications device
while operating a motor vehicle unless the vehicle is lawfully stationary. Provides enhanced
penalties when a violation occurs in a school zone or highway construction zone.
Proposed law retains present law.
Proposed law defines "school zone" as any designated area adjacent to a public or private
kindergarten through 12th grade school or postsecondary institution that is properly marked
with official school warning or similar traffic control signage, including signage provided
in Chapter 7 of the Dept. of Transportation and Development Traffic Engineering Manual
relating to schools, and extending not less than 250 feet prior to the beginning of the zone.
Proposed law specifies that a school zone is in effect 60 minutes before school starts, 60
minutes after school starts, 60 minutes before school ends, and 60 minutes after school ends.
Present law provides a definition of "Wireless telecommunications device".
Proposed law retains present law.
(Amends R.S. 32:59(A)(5); Adds R.S. 32:59(A)(6))
